        <h3 class="reqtitle">Requirement 9</h3>
        <p class="reqbody"><strong>(A) Find out about three career opportunities in the field of communication. (B) Pick one and find out the (i) education, (ii) training, and (iii) experience required for this profession. Discuss this with your counselor, and explain why this profession might interest you.</strong>
        <br>
        <br>
        <i>(A) Three career opportunities are:</i>
        </p>
        <ol class="reqbody">
            <li>Advertiser</li>
            <li>Broadcast Journalist</li>
            <li>Journalist</li>
        </ol>
        <br>
        <p class="reqbody"><i>(B) I've chosen to look further into a career as a broadcast journalist. (Information source: <a href="//study.com/how_to_become_a_broadcaster.html">study.com</a>)</i></p>
        <ol type="i" class="reqbody">
            <li>The education required to go into broadcasting is a full bachelor's degree in Communications and/or Journalism</li>
            <li>Training in newswriting and research, photojournalism (radio broadcasting exempt), and radio/television programming and production are recommended.</li>
            <li>Internships are recommended; experience working on school/local newspapers or radio stations may be required.</li>
        </ol>
